TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hart, Oliver
AU  - Moore, John
T1  - Contracts as Reference Points*
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/02/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2008.123.1.1
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 123
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 48
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We argue that a contract provides a reference point for a trading relationship: more precisely, for parties' feelings of entitlement. A party's ex post performance depends on whether he gets what he is entitled to relative to outcomes permitted by the contract. A party who is shortchanged shades on performance. A flexible contract allows parties to adjust their outcomes to uncertainty but causes inefficient shading. Our analysis provides a basis for long-term contracts in the absence of noncontractible investments and elucidates why “employment” contracts, which fix wages in advance and allow the employer to choose the task, can be optimal.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2008.123.1.1
ER  - 



